## Architecture rules
- src/index.js is the production entry point (Wrangler `main`).
- All business logic lives in src/ as focused modules.
- Never hardcode workspace_id, tenant_id, email addresses, or secret values.
- Agent Sam: D1 is canonical operational state; Supabase is the required observability mirror. Full lifecycle, tables, and required end-of-change alignment report: `.cursor/rules/agentsam-d1-supabase-alignment.mdc` (always applied).

## Deploy — never guess (wrong command = wasted work)
- `git push main` — CF Builds auto-deploys Worker only (no R2 dashboard bundle).
- `npm run deploy` — Worker/API only (src/). No R2 upload; does not refresh dashboard assets.
- `npm run deploy:frontend` or `npm run deploy:full` — same path: clean `npm run build:vite-only`, `bump-cache.js`, R2 sync, Worker via `scripts/deploy-frontend.sh`. Never set `SKIP_VITE_BUILD` for production paths; the deploy scripts reject it.
- `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml` — Worker-only one-liner.

## Sandbox is DISCONTINUED
- Never suggest deploy-sandbox.sh or promote-to-prod.sh — both are marked dangerous/discontinued.
- Deploy dashboard assets with `npm run deploy:frontend` (or `deploy:full`, same script).

## Dashboard build rules
- NEVER run cd dashboard
- Always use `npm run build:vite-only` from repo root (never `cd dashboard`).

CF Builds auto-deploys Worker on push to main. Does NOT upload R2 frontend bundle.
Run `npm run deploy:frontend` (or `deploy:full`) locally when dashboard changes need to be live immediately.

## Dashboard health vs Worker health

See `docs/agentsam_knowledge/dashboard_r2_asset_deploy_tactics.md`.

- `/health` 200 only proves Worker/API is alive — not that the dashboard works.
- Blank dashboard + JS bundle 404s (`/static/dashboard/app/*.js`) means R2 dashboard assets are missing or stale.
- `git push main` / CF Builds may deploy Worker only; it does not sync `dashboard/dist` to R2.
- Fix: `npm run deploy:frontend` (or `npm run deploy:full` for full releases). Do not recommend Worker rollback when the issue is missing Vite chunks in R2.
- Deploy validation must check `/health` **and** that dashboard HTML-referenced asset URLs return 200 (future: `scripts/verify_dashboard_asset_integrity.py`).
